            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3ESolomon%20had%20a%20vision%20to%20build%20the%20most%20magnificent%20temple%20in%20history%2C%20and%20his%20success%20resulted%20from%20the%20blessing%20of%20the%20Lord.%20First%2C%20the%20Lord%20gave%20Solomon%20wisdom%20to%20achieve%20his%20purpose%20(1%20Kings%205%3A12).%20He%20showed%20him%20how%20to%20rotate%20his%20labor%20force%20in%20such%20a%20way%20that%20the%20men%20could%20be%20in%20Lebanon%20one%20month%20and%20at%20home%20for%20two%20months.%20Shared%20responsibility%2C%20as%20indicated%20by%20rotating%20the%20labor%20force%2C%20was%20a%20wise%20plan%20from%20God%20to%20cover%20responsibilities%20without%20burning%20out%20the%20laborers.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESecond%2C%20Solomon%20achieved%20success%20because%20he%20followed%20the%20plan%20of%20the%20Lord%20(1%20Kings%206%3A12).%20You%20cannot%20hope%20to%20succeed%20at%20any%20work%20for%20God%20if%20you%20deviate%20from%20the%20revelation%20in%20the%20Bible.%20All%20work%20must%20follow%20the%20exact%20plan%20of%20the%20Church%20as%20given%20in%20the%20Gospels%2C%20Acts%2C%20and%20the%20Epistles.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFinally%2C%20Solomon%20succeeded%20because%20he%20persevered.%20He%20spent%20seven%20years%20building%20the%20temple%20(1%20Kings%206%3A38)%2C%20never%20wavering%20from%20his%20goal.%20Never%20give%20up%20when%20God%20is%20%22building%22%20with%20you.%20Though%20it%20may%20seem%20your%20work%20is%20moving%20at%20a%20crawl%2C%20keep%20doing%20what%20you%20know%20to%20do.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPurpose%2C%20plan%2C%20and%20persevere%2C%20and%20the%20Lord%20will%20build%20your%20house!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Kings.5:1-6:38",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E1%20Kings%205%3A1-6%3A38%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_1%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Kings%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EPreparations%20for%20Building%20the%20Temple%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E5%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Verses%205%3A1-18%20are%20numbered%205%3A15-32%20in%20Hebrew%20text.%3C%2Fspan%3EKing%20Hiram%20of%20Tyre%20had%20always%20been%20a%20loyal%20friend%20of%20David.%20When%20Hiram%20learned%20that%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20son%20Solomon%20was%20the%20new%20king%20of%20Israel%2C%20he%20sent%20ambassadors%20to%20congratulate%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_2%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Solomon%20sent%20this%20message%20back%20to%20Hiram%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_3%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BYou%20know%20that%20my%20father%2C%20David%2C%20was%20not%20able%20to%20build%20a%20Temple%20to%20honor%20the%20name%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20his%20God%20because%20of%20the%20many%20wars%20waged%20against%20him%20by%20surrounding%20nations.%20He%20could%20not%20build%20until%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20gave%20him%20victory%20over%20all%20his%20enemies.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_4%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20now%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20my%20God%20has%20given%20me%20peace%20on%20every%20side%3B%20I%20have%20no%20enemies%2C%20and%20all%20is%20well.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_5%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20I%20am%20planning%20to%20build%20a%20Temple%20to%20honor%20the%20name%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20my%20God%2C%20just%20as%20he%20had%20instructed%20my%20father%2C%20David.%20For%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20told%20him%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BYour%20son%2C%20whom%20I%20will%20place%20on%20your%20throne%2C%20will%20build%20the%20Temple%20to%20honor%20my%20name.%26%23x2019%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_6%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BTherefore%2C%20please%20command%20that%20cedars%20from%20Lebanon%20be%20cut%20for%20me.%20Let%20my%20men%20work%20alongside%20yours%2C%20and%20I%20will%20pay%20your%20men%20whatever%20wages%20you%20ask.%20As%20you%20know%2C%20there%20is%20no%20one%20among%20us%20who%20can%20cut%20timber%20like%20you%20Sidonians!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_7%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Hiram%20received%20Solomon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20message%2C%20he%20was%20very%20pleased%20and%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BPraise%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20today%20for%20giving%20David%20a%20wise%20son%20to%20be%20king%20of%20the%20great%20nation%20of%20Israel.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_8%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20he%20sent%20this%20reply%20to%20Solomon%3A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-body-fl-sp%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BI%20have%20received%20your%20message%2C%20and%20I%20will%20supply%20all%20the%20cedar%20and%20cypress%20timber%20you%20need.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_9%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EMy%20servants%20will%20bring%20the%20logs%20from%20the%20Lebanon%20mountains%20to%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E5%3A9%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20sea.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20make%20them%20into%20rafts%20and%20float%20them%20along%20the%20coast%20to%20whatever%20place%20you%20choose.%20Then%20we%20will%20break%20the%20rafts%20apart%20so%20you%20can%20carry%20the%20logs%20away.%20You%20can%20pay%20me%20by%20supplying%20me%20with%20food%20for%20my%20household.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_10%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Hiram%20supplied%20as%20much%20cedar%20and%20cypress%20timber%20as%20Solomon%20desired.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_11%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20return%2C%20Solomon%20sent%20him%20an%20annual%20payment%20of%20100%2C000%20bushels%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E5%3A11a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3E20%2C000%20cors%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B4%2C400%20kiloliters%5D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20wheat%20for%20his%20household%20and%20110%2C000%20gallons%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E5%3A11b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%2C%20which%20reads%20%3Cem%3E20%2C000%20baths%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B420%26%23xA0%3Bkiloliters%5D%20(see%20also%202%26%23xA0%3BChr%202%3A10)%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3E20%26%23xA0%3Bcors%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%201%2C000%26%23xA0%3Bgallons%20or%204.4%26%23xA0%3Bkiloliters%20in%20volume.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20of%20pure%20olive%20oil.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_12%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20gave%20wisdom%20to%20Solomon%2C%20just%20as%20he%20had%20promised.%20And%20Hiram%20and%20Solomon%20made%20a%20formal%20alliance%20of%20peace.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_13%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20King%20Solomon%20conscripted%20a%20labor%20force%20of%2030%2C000%20men%20from%20all%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_14%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20sent%20them%20to%20Lebanon%20in%20shifts%2C%2010%2C000%20every%20month%2C%20so%20that%20each%20man%20would%20be%20one%20month%20in%20Lebanon%20and%20two%20months%20at%20home.%20Adoniram%20was%20in%20charge%20of%20this%20labor%20force.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_15%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3ESolomon%20also%20had%2070%2C000%20common%20laborers%2C%2080%2C000%20quarry%20workers%20in%20the%20hill%20country%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_16%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%203%2C600%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E5%3A16%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20some%20Greek%20manuscripts%20(see%20also%202%26%23xA0%3BChr%202%3A2%2C%2018)%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3E3%2C300.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20foremen%20to%20supervise%20the%20work.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_17%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20command%2C%20they%20quarried%20large%20blocks%20of%20high-quality%20stone%20and%20shaped%20them%20to%20make%20the%20foundation%20of%20the%20Temple.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_5_18%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%225%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EMen%20from%20the%20city%20of%20Gebal%20helped%20Solomon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20and%20Hiram%26%23x2019%3Bs%20builders%20prepare%20the%20timber%20and%20stone%20for%20the%20Temple.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_6_1%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%226%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Kings%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ESolomon%20Builds%20the%20Temple%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EIt%20was%20in%20midspring%2C%20in%20the%20month%20of%20Ziv%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E6%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EIt%20was%20in%20the%20month%20of%20Ziv%2C%20which%20is%20the%20second%20month.%3C%2Fem%3E%20This%20month%20of%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar%20usually%20occurs%20within%20the%20months%20of%20April%20and%20May.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20during%20the%20fourth%20year%20of%20Solomon%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%2C%20that%20he%20began%20to%20construct%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20This%20was%20480%26%23xA0%3Byears%20after%20the%20people%20of%20Israel%20were%20rescued%20from%20their%20slavery%20in%20the%20land%20of%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_6_2%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%226%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20Temple%20that%20King%20Solomon%20built%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20was%2090%26%23xA0%3Bfeet%20long%2C%2030%26%23xA0%3Bfeet%20wide%2C%20and%2045%26%23xA0%3Bfeet%20high.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E6%3A2%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3E60%26%23xA0%3Bcubits%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B27.6%26%23xA0%3Bmeters%5D%20%3Cem%3Elong%2C%2020%26%23xA0%3Bcubits%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B9.2%26%23xA0%3Bmeters%5D%20%3Cem%3Ewide%2C%20and%2030%26%23xA0%3Bcubits%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B13.8%26%23xA0%3Bmeters%5D%20%3Cem%3Ehigh.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_6_3%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%226%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20entry%20room%20at%20the%20front%20of%20the%20Temple%20was%2030%26%23xA0%3Bfeet%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E6%3A3a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3E20%26%23xA0%3Bcubits%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B9.2%26%23xA0%3Bmeters%5D%3B%20also%20in%206%3A16%2C%2020.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20wide%2C%20running%20across%20the%20entire%20width%20of%20the%20Temple.%20It%20projected%20outward%2015%26%23xA0%3Bfeet%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E6%3A3b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3E10%26%23xA0%3Bcubits%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B4.6%26%23xA0%3Bmeters%5D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20from%20the%20front%20of%20the%20Temple.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_6_4%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%226%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3ESolomon%20also%20made%20narrow%20recessed%20windows%20throughout%20the%20Temple.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_6_5%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%226%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20built%20a%20complex%20of%20rooms%20against%20the%20outer%20walls%20of%20the%20Temple%2C%20all%20the%20way%20around%20the%20sides%20and%20rear%20of%20the%20building.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_6_6%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%226%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20complex%20was%20three%20stories%20high%2C%20the%20bottom%20floor%20being%207%3Csup%20class%3D%22fract-num%22%3E1%3C%2Fsup%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22fract-slash%22%3E%2F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22fract-den%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3Bfeet%20wide%2C%20the%20second%20floor%209%26%23xA0%3Bfeet%20wide%2C%20and%20the%20top%20floor%2010%3Csup%20class%3D%22fract-num%22%3E1%3C%2Fsup%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22fract-slash%22%3E%2F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22fract-den%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3Bfeet%20wide.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E6%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20bottom%20floor%20being%205%26%23xA0%3Bcubits%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B2.3%26%23xA0%3Bmeters%5D%20%3Cem%3Ewide%2C%20the%20second%20floor%206%26%23xA0%3Bcubits%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B2.8%26%23xA0%3Bmeters%5D%20%3Cem%3Ewide%2C%20and%20the%20top%20floor%207%26%23xA0%3Bcubits%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B3.2%26%23xA0%3Bmeters%5D%20%3Cem%3Ewide%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20rooms%20were%20connected%20to%20the%20walls%20of%20the%20Temple%20by%20beams%20resting%20on%20ledges%20built%20out%20from%20the%20wall.%20So%20the%20beams%20were%20not%20inserted%20into%20the%20walls%20themselves.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_6_7%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%226%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20stones%20used%20in%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Temple%20were%20finished%20at%20the%20quarry%2C%20so%20there%20was%20no%20sound%20of%20hammer%2C%20ax%2C%20or%20any%20other%20iron%20tool%20at%20the%20building%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_6_8%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%226%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20entrance%20to%20the%20bottom%20floor%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E6%3A8%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3Emiddle%20floor.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20was%20on%20the%20south%20side%20of%20the%20Temple.%20There%20were%20winding%20stairs%20going%20up%20to%20the%20second%20floor%2C%20and%20another%20flight%20of%20stairs%20between%20the%20second%20and%20third%20floors.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_6_9%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%226%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20completing%20the%20Temple%20structure%2C%20Solomon%20put%20in%20a%20ceiling%20made%20of%20cedar%20beams%20and%20planks.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_6_10%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%226%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20already%20stated%2C%20he%20built%20a%20complex%20of%20rooms%20along%20the%20sides%20of%20the%20building%2C%20attached%20to%20the%20Temple%20walls%20by%20cedar%20timbers.%20Each%20story%20of%20the%20complex%20was%207%3Csup%20class%3D%22fract-num%22%3E1%3C%2Fsup%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22fract-slash%22%3E%2F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22fract-den%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3Bfeet%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E6%3A10%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3E5%26%23xA0%3Bcubits%3C%2Fem%3E%20%5B2.3%26%23xA0%3Bmeters%5D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20high.%3C%2Fverse_export%3