EThe%20second%20time%20they%20went%2C%20Joseph%20revealed%20his%20identity%20to%20his%20brothers%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E7%3A13%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Other%20manuscripts%20read%20%3Cem%3EJoseph%20was%20recognized%20by%20his%20brothers.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20they%20were%20introduced%20to%20Pharaoh.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_14%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Joseph%20sent%20for%20his%20father%2C%20Jacob%2C%20and%20all%20his%20relatives%20to%20come%20to%20Egypt%2C%20seventy-five%20persons%20in%20all.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_15%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Jacob%20went%20to%20Egypt.%20He%20died%20there%2C%20as%20did%20our%20ancestors.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_16%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3ETheir%20bodies%20were%20taken%20to%20Shechem%20and%20buried%20in%20the%20tomb%20Abraham%20had%20bought%20for%20a%20certain%20price%20from%20Hamor%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sons%20in%20Shechem.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_17%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BAs%20the%20time%20drew%20near%20when%20God%20would%20fulfill%20his%20promise%20to%20Abraham%2C%20the%20number%20of%20our%20people%20in%20Egypt%20greatly%20increased.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_18%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20then%20a%20new%20king%20came%20to%20the%20throne%20of%20Egypt%20who%20knew%20nothing%20about%20Joseph.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_19%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20king%20exploited%20our%20people%20and%20oppressed%20them%2C%20forcing%20parents%20to%20abandon%20their%20newborn%20babies%20so%20they%20would%20die.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_20%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BAt%20that%20time%20Moses%20was%20born%26%23x2014%3Ba%20beautiful%20child%20in%20God%26%23x2019%3Bs%20eyes.%20His%20parents%20cared%20for%20him%20at%20home%20for%20three%20months.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_21%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20they%20had%20to%20abandon%20him%2C%20Pharaoh%26%23x2019%3Bs%20daughter%20adopted%20him%20and%20raised%20him%20as%20her%20own%20son.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_22%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EMoses%20was%20taught%20all%20the%20wisdom%20of%20the%20Egyptians%2C%20and%20he%20was%20powerful%20in%20both%20speech%20and%20action.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_23%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BOne%20day%20when%20Moses%20was%20forty%20years%20old%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20visit%20his%20relatives%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_24%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20saw%20an%20Egyptian%20mistreating%20an%20Israelite.%20So%20Moses%20came%20to%20the%20man%26%23x2019%3Bs%20defense%20and%20avenged%20him%2C%20killing%20the%20Egyptian.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_25%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3EMoses%20assumed%20his%20fellow%20Israelites%20would%20realize%20that%20God%20had%20sent%20him%20to%20rescue%20them%2C%20but%20they%20didn%26%23x2019%3Bt.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_26%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BThe%20next%20day%20he%20visited%20them%20again%20and%20saw%20two%20men%20of%20Israel%20fighting.%20He%20tried%20to%20be%20a%20peacemaker.%20%26%23x2018%3BMen%2C%26%23x2019%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26%23x2018%3Byou%20are%20brothers.%20Why%20are%20you%20fighting%20each%20other%3F%26%23x2019%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_27%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BBut%20the%20man%20in%20the%20wrong%20pushed%20Moses%20aside.%20%26%23x2018%3BWho%20made%20you%20a%20ruler%20and%20judge%20over%20us%3F%26%23x2019%3B%20he%20asked.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_28%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E28%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2018%3BAre%20you%20going%20to%20kill%20me%20as%20you%20killed%20that%20Egyptian%20yesterday%3F%26%23x2019%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22acts_7_29%22%20bk%3D%22acts%22%20ch%3D%227%22%20vn%3D%2229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E29%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Moses%20heard%20that%2C%20he%20fled%20the%20country%20and%20lived%20as%20a%20foreigner%20in%20the%20land%20of%20Midian.%20There%20his%20two%20sons%20were%20born.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E"
